class Solution {
    public char kthCharacter(long k, int[] operations) {
        long length = 1;
        int shift = 0;
        for (int op : operations) {
            length *= 2;
            if (op == 1) shift++;
        }
        while (k > 0) {
            if (k > length / 2) {
                k -= length / 2;
                shift++;
            }
            length /= 2;
        }
        return (char) ('a' + (shift - 1) % 26);
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution iterates through the operations to track the length of the final string and the number of shifts. It then uses a while loop to find the kth character by determining whether it falls in the first or second half of the string at each operation, effectively reducing the problem size by half at each step.
